Data Design
• Design a corresponding Entity-Relationship Model for the corresponding sales application
• For each entity define a senseful number of attribute including an unique key

Data explorer:
• Create a schema “SALES”
• Create a user group: “SALES_USER_GROUP”
• Create roles: “SALES_ADMIN” , “SALES_MANAGER”, “SALES_REPRESENTATIVE”
• Create users: SALE_ADMIN, SALES_MANAGER_1, UNI_REPRENTATIVE_1
• Grant privileges
• Create corresponding tables (primary key, foreign key, mandatory vs. optional attributes)
• Populate tables with a senseful number of test data records
• Create views: CATEGORY_PRODUCT_VIEW, SALES_REPRESENTATIVE_VIEW
• Create functions: AVERAGE_SALES_PER_CUSTOMER, AVERAGE_SALES_PER_SALES_REPRENSATIVE

Business Application Studio:
• Create a calculation view: CVIEW_TOP_5_CATEGORIES_SOLD
• Create a calculation view: CVIEW_AVG_SALES_ORDER_PRICE_PER_CUSTOMER
• Create a calculation view: CVIEW_TOP_3_SALES_REPRENSTATIVES
